HEADWORD: Chondroganoidea
<hw>Chon`dro*ga*noi"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>cho`ndros</grk> cartilage + NL. <ets>ganoidei</ets>. See
<er>Ganoid</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of ganoid
fishes, including the sturgeons; -- so called on account of their
cartilaginous skeleton.</def>⟦br⟧
